            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://fediscience.org/@petergleick\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>petergleick</span></a></span><br>&gt;It's now a question of how bad are we going to allow it to get.</p><p>-----<br>We're not doing anything except make it worse more quickly, so it's not unrealistic to expect the \"make it worse\" to continue.  All we get is bullshit non solutions like ecars and empty promises, with the occasional photo of a wind tribunes or solar panel and some asshat on a cruise ships in the artic reporting about how dire it is.</p><p>Even flat lining emsisons is a massive failure.</p><p>----</p><p>&gt;Stop burning fossil fuels.</p><p>And until that great and glorious day we need to .. stop emitting CO2, now,  so stop we need to stop flying, stop driving, stop flying horses around the world to jump over some sticks, ban cruise ships, personal water craft etc and most importantly vote for politcans who would enact legislation to force the recalcitrant to do the same.</p><p>Alas not being a high emitting asshat is beyod the willingness of high emitters, so, it's back to pearl clutching and watching emissions increase.</p>",
